This paper is primarily focused on object detection in images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of deep learning models and neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the use of JPEG compression, which could potentially place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) categories.
